title: Grateful Dead Live at Augusta Civic Center on 1984-10-12
lineage: MAC > Nak CR7A w/ azimuth adjusted > Korg MR-1000 @ 5.8mhz > FLAC 24/96; Edited & Mastered in Audacity by Joe Noel > Flac 24/96; Checksum & tags created in xACT
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, It Must Have Been The Roses, On The Road Again, Jack A Roe, It's All Over Now, Cumberland Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Don't Need Love-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Playin' Reprise-> Uncle John's Band-> Morning Dew, E: Good Lovin'

final/last "On the Road Again": 04-19-83
last "Jack-A-Roe": 04-17-82

reviews.review_text: Thank you for your part! These tapes I made of the GD in 83 and 84 had a long journey and a lot of good people took part in getting them here. Thanks to all!
Very Good Audience Recording I rate this slightly higher than the Oade audience tape, but it's a close call.
